              "content": "# Decode Settlement Calldata\n\nDecode hex-encoded `Settlement.settle()` calldata into readable fields, or fully reconstruct the original `/solve` request and response.\n\n**User argument**: $ARGUMENTS (calldata hex string starting with `0x`, or \"help\")\n\nIf the argument is \"help\" or empty, explain both decoding levels. If a calldata hex is provided, decode it and display the results.\n\n---\n\n## Two Decoding Levels\n\nThe SDK provides two levels of decoding:\n\n### Level 1: `decodeSettleCalldata()` — Raw On-Chain Types\n\nDecodes ABI-encoded calldata back to SDK on-chain types (`Trade`, `bigint` flags, etc.). This is a direct ABI decode with no interpretation.\n\n### Level 2: `reconstructFromCalldata()` — API-Level Types\n\nGoes further: unpacks flag bitmasks, decodes trade flags, recovers executed amounts from clearing prices, and restores the original `SolveRequest` / `SolveResponse` structure.\n\n---\n\n## Level 1: decodeSettleCalldata\n\n```typescript\nimport { decodeSettleCalldata } from '@okx-intent-swap/sdk-solver';\n\nconst decoded = decodeSettleCalldata('0x...');\n\n// Returns:\n// {\n//   settleId: bigint,\n//   tokens: string[],                              // checksummed addresses\n//   clearingPrices: bigint[],                       // parallel to tokens[]\n//   trades: Trade[],                                // on-chain struct format\n//   interactions: [Interaction[], Interaction[], Interaction[]],\n//   surplusFeeInfo: { feePercent: bigint, trimReceiver: string, flag: bigint }\n// }\n```\n\n### Inspecting Decoded Fields\n\n```typescript\nconsole.log('Settle ID:', decoded.settleId);\nconsole.log('Tokens:', decoded.tokens);\nconsole.log('Clearing Prices:', decoded.clearingPrices.map(String));\n\nfor (const trade of decoded.trades) {\n  console.log('---');\n  console.log('From token index:', trade.fromTokenAddressIndex);\n  console.log('To token index:', trade.toTokenAddressIndex);\n  console.log('Owner:', trade.owner);\n  console.log('Receiver:', trade.receiver);  // address(0) means same as owner\n  console.log('From amount:', trade.fromTokenAmount);\n  console.log('To amount:', trade.toTokenAmount);\n  console.log('Executed amount:', trade.executedAmount);\n  console.log('Flags:', trade.flags);        // packed bitmask (see below)\n  console.log('Commission count:', trade.commissionInfos.length);\n  console.log('Solver fee %:', trade.solverFeeInfo.feePercent);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Flag Unpacking\n\n### Commission Info Flags\n\nThe `flag` field in `CommissionInfo` is a packed `uint256` bitmask:\n\n```\nbit 255: FROM_TOKEN_COMMISSION (feeDirection = true)\nbit 254: TO_TOKEN_COMMISSION   (feeDirection = false)\nbit 253: IS_TO_B               (toB = true)\nbit 248: LABEL_OKX             (commissionType = \"okx\")\nbit 247: LABEL_PARENT          (commissionType = \"parent\")\nbit 246: LABEL_CHILD           (commissionType = \"child\")\n```\n\nUse `unpackCommissionFlag()` to extract:\n\n```typescript\nimport { unpackCommissionFlag } from '@okx-intent-swap/sdk-solver';\n\nfor (const trade of decoded.trades) {\n  for (const ci of trade.commissionInfos) {\n    const { feeDirection, toB, commissionType } = unpackCommissionFlag(ci.flag);\n    console.log({\n      feePercent: ci.feePercent,\n      referrer: ci.referrerWalletAddress,\n      feeDirection,      // true = fromToken\n      toB,               // true = Settlement pays\n      commissionType,    // \"okx\" | \"parent\" | \"child\" | \"\"\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Solver Fee Flags\n\n```typescript\nimport { unpackSolverFeeFlag } from '@okx-intent-swap/sdk-solver';\n\nconst feeDirection = unpackSolverFeeFlag(trade.solverFeeInfo.flag);\n// true = fromToken, false = toToken\n```\n\n### Trade Flags\n\nThe `trade.flags` field packs swap mode, partial fill, and signing scheme:\n\n```\nbit 0:   reserved (exactIn = 0)\nbit 1:   partiallyFillable (1 = partial, 0 = fill-or-kill)\nbits 5-6: signingScheme (0 = eip712, 1 = ethSign, 2 = eip1271, 3 = preSign)\n```\n\n```typescript\nimport { decodeTradeFlags } from '@okx-intent-swap/sdk-common';\n\nconst { swapMode, partiallyFillable, signingScheme } = decodeTradeFlags(trade.flags);\nconsole.log({ swapMode, partiallyFillable, signingScheme });\n// { swapMode: \"exactIn\", partiallyFillable: false, signingScheme: 0 }\n```\n\n---\n\n## Level 2: reconstructFromCalldata\n\n```typescript\nimport { reconstructFromCalldata } from '@okx-intent-swap/sdk-solver';\n\nconst { request, response, interactions } = reconstructFromCalldata('0x...');\n\n// request: SolveRequest  — reconstructed /solve request\n// response: SolveResponse — reconstructed /solve response\n// interactions: [Interaction[], Interaction[], Interaction[]]\n```\n\n### What It Recovers\n\n| Field | Recovery Method |\n|-------|----------------|\n| `auctionId` | Direct from `settleId` |\n| `fromTokenAddress` / `toTokenAddress` | `tokens[trade.fromTokenAddressIndex]` |\n| `receiver` | `address(0)` restored to `owner` |\n| `swapMode`, `partiallyFillable`, `signingScheme` | Decoded from `trade.flags` bitmask |\n| `commissionInfos` | Flag unpacked via `unpackCommissionFlag()` |\n| `solverFeeInfo.feeDirection` | Unpacked via `unpackSolverFeeFlag()` |\n| `executedFromTokenAmount` / `executedToTokenAmount` | Computed from clearing prices + fees |\n| `clearingPrices` (response) | On-chain uint256 values as decimal strings |\n\n### Executed Amount Recovery Logic\n\nFor `exactIn` orders (`executedAmount = eS`):\n- **fromToken fees or no fees**: `eB = clearingPrices[fromTokenIndex]`\n- **toToken fees**: `toGross = clearingPrices[fromTokenIndex]`, then `eB = toGross - totalToTokenFee`\n\nFor `exactOut` orders (`executedAmount = eB`):\n- **toToken fees or no fees**: `eS = clearingPrices[toTokenIndex]`\n- **fromToken fees**: Reverse-computed from fee percentages\n\n### Limitations\n\n1. **Assumes `useComputedPrices=true`**: The SDK default. If calldata was built with `useComputedPrices=false`, the reconstructed executed amounts may not match.\n2. **Clearing prices are uint256**: The response `clearingPrices` are on-chain values, not the original decimal strings from the API.\n3. **`solverFeeInfo.feeAmount` is recomputed**: The original API `feeAmount` is not stored on-chain; it is recalculated from `feePercent` and base amount.\n4. **Addresses are checksummed**: ethers v5 decode returns checksummed addresses. Compare with `.toLowerCase()` for equality checks.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Example\n\n```typescript\nimport {\n  decodeSettleCalldata,\n  reconstructFromCalldata,\n  unpackCommissionFlag,\n  unpackSolverFeeFlag,\n} from '@okx-intent-swap/sdk-solver';\nimport { decodeTradeFlags } from '@okx-intent-swap/sdk-common';\n\nconst calldata = '0x...';  // hex-encoded settle() calldata\n\n// === Level 1: Raw decode ===\nconst decoded = decodeSettleCalldata(calldata);\n\nconsole.log('=== Level 1: Raw On-Chain Data ===');\nconsole.log('Settle ID:', decoded.settleId.toString());\nconsole.log('Token count:', decoded.tokens.length);\nconsole.log('Trade count:', decoded.trades.length);\n\nfor (let i = 0; i \u003c decoded.trades.length; i++) {\n  const trade = decoded.trades[i];\n  const fromToken = decoded.tokens[trade.fromTokenAddressIndex];\n  const toToken = decoded.tokens[trade.toTokenAddressIndex];\n\n  console.log(`\\nTrade ${i}:`);\n  console.log(`  ${fromToken} → ${toToken}`);\n  console.log(`  Owner: ${trade.owner}`);\n  console.log(`  From amount: ${trade.fromTokenAmount}`);\n  console.log(`  To amount: ${trade.toTokenAmount}`);\n  console.log(`  Executed: ${trade.executedAmount}`);\n\n  // Unpack flags\n  const { swapMode, partiallyFillable, signingScheme } = decodeTradeFlags(trade.flags);\n  console.log(`  Mode: ${swapMode}, partial: ${partiallyFillable}, scheme: ${signingScheme}`);\n\n  // Commission flags\n  for (const ci of trade.commissionInfos) {\n    const unpacked = unpackCommissionFlag(ci.flag);\n    console.log(`  Commission: ${ci.feePercent} (${unpacked.commissionType}, dir=${unpacked.feeDirection}, toB=${unpacked.toB})`);\n  }\n\n  // Solver fee\n  const solverDir = unpackSolverFeeFlag(trade.solverFeeInfo.flag);\n  console.log(`  Solver fee: ${trade.solverFeeInfo.feePercent} (dir=${solverDir})`);\n}\n\n// === Level 2: Reconstruct API objects ===\nconst { request, response, interactions } = reconstructFromCalldata(calldata);\n\nconsole.log('\\n=== Level 2: Reconstructed API Data ===');\nconsole.log('Auction ID:', request.auctionId);\nconsole.log('Orders:', request.orders.length);\n\nfor (let i = 0; i \u003c request.orders.length; i++) {\n  const reqOrder = request.orders[i];\n  const resOrder = response.solutions[0].orders[i];\n\n  console.log(`\\nOrder ${i}:`);\n  console.log(`  ${reqOrder.fromTokenAddress} → ${reqOrder.toTokenAddress}`);\n  console.log(`  Executed: ${resOrder.executedFromTokenAmount} → ${resOrder.executedToTokenAmount}`);\n  console.log(`  Solver fee amount: ${resOrder.solverFeeInfo.feeAmount}`);\n}\n\n// Interactions\nconst totalInteractions = interactions.flat().length;\nconsole.log(`\\nInteractions: ${totalInteractions} total`);\nfor (let phase = 0; phase \u003c 3; phase++) {\n  if (interactions[phase].length \u003e 0) {\n    console.log(`  Phase ${phase}: ${interactions[phase].length} calls`);\n    for (const ix of interactions[phase]) {\n      console.log(`    target=${ix.target}, value=${ix.value}, data=${ix.callData.slice(0, 10)}...`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Build Commands Reference\n\n```bash\npnpm install                  # Install dependencies\npnpm build                    # Build all packages\npnpm typecheck                # Type-check all packages\n```\n",
