ront-loading**: High-risk / uncertain items in early phases\n\n### 3. Task Specification\n\nFor non-trivial tasks, provide detail:\n\n```markdown\n### Task N.M: [Name]\n\n**Input**: What must exist before starting\n**Output**: What will exist after completion\n**Steps**:\n1. Concrete action 1\n2. Concrete action 2\n3. ...\n\n**Verification**:\n- Command to run: `make validate`\n- Expected output: \"All checks passed\"\n\n**Files to create/modify**:\n- `path/to/file.ext` — description of changes\n```\n\n### 4. Dependency Graph\n\nVisualize task dependencies:\n\n```\nPhase 1: [1.1] → [1.2] → [1.3]\n                    ↓\nPhase 2:         [2.1] → [2.2]\n                    ↓\nPhase 3:         [3.1] → [3.2] → [3.3]\n```\n\n### 5. Risk Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Phase | Impact | Mitigation | Trigger |\n|------|-------|--------|------------|---------|\n| ... | N | High | Fallback approach | If X happens |\n\n### 6. Verification Matrix\n\nMap deliverables to verification methods:\n\n| Deliverable | Verification | Automated |\n|-------------|-------------|-----------|\n| Repository structure | `ls` + directory check | Yes (CI) |\n| SKILL.md format | `validate.sh` | Yes (CI) |\n| Install workflow | `make install` + verify symlinks | Semi |\n| Content quality | PR review | No |\n\n### 7. Rollback Strategy\n\nFor each phase, describe how to undo if things go wrong:\n\n| Phase | Rollback Method |\n|-------|----------------|\n| 1 | Delete repo, no external impact |\n| 2 | Revert CI config, remove scripts |\n| 3 | `make uninstall` removes symlinks |\n\n## Quality Criteria\n\n- [ ] Every phase has explicit exit criteria\n- [ ] Every task has a verification method\n- [ ] Dependencies are documented (no implicit ordering)\n- [ ] Deliverables are concrete artifacts (not activities)\n- [ ] Risks are tied to specific phases\n- [ ] No task is larger than can be completed and verified in one session\n- [ ] Rollback path exists for each phase\n\n## Style Guidelines\n\n- Use imperative verbs for tasks (\"Create\", \"Configure\", \"Write\")\n- Deliverables are nouns (\"README.md\", \"CI pipeline\", \"install target\")\n- Verification is always a concrete action with expected result\n- Number tasks as `Phase.Task` (e.g., 1.1, 1.2, 2.1)\n- Keep each phase to 3-7 tasks (split if larger)\n- Use checkboxes for deliverables (trackable progress)\n\n## Phase Template\n\nWhen generating, use this template per phase:\n\n```markdown\n## Phase N: [Name]\n\n**Goal**: [One sentence]\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- [ ] [Artifact 1]\n- [ ] [Artifact 2]\n\n**Tasks**:\n\n| # | Task | Depends On | Verification |\n|---|------|-----------|-------------|\n| N.1 | [Action verb] + [object] | - | [How to verify] |\n| N.2 | [Action verb] + [object] | N.1 | [How to verify] |\n\n**Exit Criteria**:\n- [Condition 1 that must be true]\n- [Condition 2 that must be true]\n```\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. Read Spec (required), PRD, BRD for full context\n2. Identify natural phase boundaries from Spec architecture\n3. Break each phase into atomic, verifiable tasks\n4. Map dependencies between tasks and phases\n5. Generate Plan following the structure above\n6. Write to `docs/plan.md` (or path specified by user)\n7. Review dependency graph for circular or missing dependencies\n",
